args: I see damage to the walls and furniture.\n▷You think there was a fight here?\nOh, wait! Look over there!◁
(Laxi hasn't noticed me. In that case...)
▷Yeah, it's definitely one of the thieves\nmentioned in the wanted notice.◁

The wounds look familiar. Referencing
past data. Deducing attacker...
▷Don't tell me the folks who did this
were...◁
▷Ayaha! Hrk!◁\nI failed to detect her attack!
Been a long time, Laxi! Sadly, it's also\nfarewell, because I'm about to pull your\ndumb head right off your dumb body!
Sustaining damage to neck components!\n▷This is bad! We can't shake her!◁
Kya ha ha ha! You're gonna be torn to\nugly little SHREDS!
It's Eirene and Finni.\n▷And just in time!◁
We were conducting a sweep of the\nhideout when we picked up a powerful\nenemy signature.
And then we came rushin' in here just\nin time to save your booties!
So it wasn't just Laxi in this place, eh?\nI assume you two are androids as well?
You're one of those twins from Agito.\nWhere is your other half?

We may be of different type and affiliation,
but we've heard about the things you've
done to our fellow androids.
Now it's payback time!
Kya ha ha! Then stop me if you can!\nI'll rip all your stupid heads off at once!
Simulation complete. Calculated pattern\nfor pincer attack. Commencing combat.
Green across the board! Fightin' time!
Get down and show me some ugly\ngroveling, puppets! KYA HA HA HA!
Oooo, this candy is yummy!\nWhat's the flavor?
Hey, so have you really not been\nshowered in holy water, Otoha?
I don't know about any of that stuff.
But if the miasma isn't making you cuckoo,\nyour body must be special in some way.
Or maybe it couldn't take your sense\nbecause you don't have any! Ah ha ha!\nThat'd be absolutely BANANAS!
Humans are basically the same as bugs,\nbut I dig folks like you who are totally nuts.
And I like folks like you. You're so\nemotionally unstable, but your way\nof thinking is WONDERFUL!
Yep! This world is my toy box and\neverything exists to entertain me.
We're free to play however I like.\nNo matter how much we destroy our toys,\nit should be allowed because we're free.
There's something wrong with the adults\nwho scold us for just breaking a toy.\nWe have to make them understand.
Okay, so how would you do that, exactly?

I'll tear off their limbs so they can't cross
me again. Then I'll rend their hearts by
destroying what's dear to them so they
can't even get angry anymore.
Oh, I like you. I like you a LOT.
Say, Otoha? You want to play with me?
I've been running riot solo lately,\nand it's got me stuck in a rut.
Well, I was kinda thinking I'd play on my\nown for a while, buuuut...
So you don't want to play with me?\nDo you maybe like being alone?
Nah, I'll play with you. At least you're not\na boring loser like Ayaha.
Damn it! I should be able to beat them\neven without the power of the mask!
The enemy has taken heavy damage.\nVictory is at hand.\n▷This will end it!◁
Enemy neutralized. Combat ended.\n▷Let's restrain her while we can.◁
Uh, wouldn't it be better to...ya know?\nFinish her off?
Otoha isn't here.\n▷We need to ask her some things,\nincluding where the other Agitos are.◁
Yeah, but this lady ain't exactly\ncooperative. You really think she'll\njust tell you?
About that, perhaps you'll be good\nenough to let me analyze her?
Commencing mana scan...\nAnalyzing biometric data...\nYes, I see.

Previous combat data revealed that their
twin coordinated attacks had a very high
synchronization rate for humans, which
raised some questions for me.
Agreed. Despite a lack of verbal\ncommunication, they managed to attack\nwith perfect timing.
And now we know why: Their horns are\nsensory organs which emit mana.
They use them to match each other's mana\nwavelengths and share thoughts and\nfeelings instantaneously.
So they were syncing their consciousness\nvia telepathy? That's a pretty amazing skill\nfor a pair of humans.
It sounds similar to the sending and\nreceiving of remote commands between\nandroids.

Yes, the mechanism is almost the same.
So if we apply that and tune our
frequencies to the mana emitted from
the horns...
We could access the twins' consciousness!
They're not androids, though, so I can't say\nfor certain it'll work.

Analyzing Eirene's proposal...
Conclusion: it is theoretically possible.
▷In which case, we can get the info we
need without trying to force Ayaha to talk!◁
It's worth a try. But who's gonna do it?
If we're essentially accessing the heart of\na human, it makes sense for Laxi to do it,\ngiven she knows much of the heart.
▷Yeah, leave it to us!◁\nAll right. We'll try.
Tuning mana wavelength. Interference\nratio 50, 70, 90... Alignment complete.\nAccessing subject's consciousness...
